Upon running, the program will ask user for 1 of 3 choices:
(1) Generate 1 random N-Queens and solve using Hill Climb and Min Conflict.
(2) Generate user choice 'n' random N-Queens and solve using Hill Clumb and Min Conflict.
(3) Exit Program.

If chosen option (1) or (2), the program will ask for the number of queens to generate. Enter your choice as an int.

If chosen option (2), the program will ask to enter the number of random puzzles. Enter your choice as an int.
The Program will then generate both searches and display the resulting boards as well as the initially generated board.
The Success rates, time of search, and step costs are displayed for each search.
